@4   = ~Long Sword of Beauty +4: Doreen
Doreen, or Do'Ree'Nelissixia as pronounced in draconic, was an ancient and proud gold dragon.  While probably the longest lived of any species in the realms, dragons too, eventually grow old and die.  When it came to be that Doreen saw her own end, she could not bear to deprive the world of her beauty.  Before she died, she passed her soul into the one object that could be like herself, beautiful and deadly at the same time, a sword.  She plucked the finest blade from her considerable hoard, and gave up her life, so to speak, into this blade.

The wielder of Doreen will find that not only is the beauty of a gold dragon passed to them, but the intelligence and wisdom of one who has lived many millennia is now at their grasp.  Fighter mages would loath to pass this blade up, and indeed, it has passed through the hands of many fighter-mages to come to yours.

Doreen has become attuned to the attitudes of blades, and may once per day, summon three dancing blades to fight for her wielder.

STATISTICS:

Intelligence +2
Wisdom +2
Charisma +2
Sword Summons: Summon 3 dancing swords once per day.  Dancing swords can attack on their own for 4 rounds.

THACO:  +4 bonus
Damage:  1D8 +4
Damage type:  slashing
Weight: 3
Speed Factor: 3
Proficiency Type: Long sword
Type:  1-handed
Requires: 6 Strength
