@17  = ~Wakizashi of Speed +2: Masa
Ma'Zathix'lithia, or Masa for short, was a young silver dragon known amongst his family as the fastest dragonling to ever walk over Faerun.  He was also known as a trickster who used his talents for quick and stealthy movement to play pranks on his siblings and steal choice bits from the older dragons to add to his own hoard.  Regardless, he was thought of in a fond light by the others of the benevolent silver dragonflight.

Sadly it was this mischievousness that led to his unfortunate demise.  Once in his travels, shapeshifted to a human form of course, he came across a group of black cloaked and hooded mages convening in a secluded grove.  Masa was uninterested in the goings on of lesser beings, but he did notice a very bright and shining gem that the mages were seemingly concentrating their magical energy into.  Masa waited patiently until the mages had finished their ceremony and had moved on to another part of the grove, when he used every stealthy trick he had learned to sneak up to procure the gem, he almost had it in his grasp when his body suddenly stiffened.  He noticed the mages looking at him, their hoods thrown back, the sight of six skeletal liches stared, it seemed, into Masa's very soul.  In a blinding light of anguish, the young dragon's soul was ripped from his body and stored in a gem much like the one he was trying to steal.  "Two of them", said one lich, "What shall be done?".  "I have a plan", said the leader.   Masa's soul was then imbued into this wakizashi, and the blade itself stored in the crypt of the evil leader of the cadre of liches.

Masa's soul has become dedicated to the fighting of evil so that acts like this are not to happen again.  Should he find a partner to aid him, they would surely be all but undefeatable.

Masa's stealth and quickness have permeated this blade, making it a coveted item for thieves all over the realms.  It increases the dexterity of the wielder as well as incrementing the stealth skill of the wielder.  Masa has no speed factor.

STATISTICS

