@18  = ~Mune +2~
@19  = ~Wakizashi of Strength +2: Mune
Mun'Ayisslith, Or Mune for short, was the one of the siblings of the silver dragon, Masa.  While Masa was quick and agile, Mune was very strong and hardy.  Mune had a very large sense of duty, and took it upon himself to see that Masa did not come into too much trouble.  His life, although short, was happy, and his death, as his life, centered around duty.

One day, while flying, Mune spotted Masa creeping around the woods in human form, he also spotted what was definitely trouble directly in his brother's path, six liches in a grove.  Masa's light frame would make him a fearsome dragon as an adult, but at his current age, he would be no match in a battle.  Mune took it upon himself to save his brother as well as rid the land of these evil undead wizards.  He swooped down and unleashed a fearsome attack, but the liches overpowered him with their magics.  "What shall we do with this zealous young drake, Kangaxx?", asked one lich to another who obviously was in charge.  "This one's soul is mine."  A blinding flash of pain and then a floating nothingness as Mune's essence was trapped in a soul stone.  After what seemed an eternity, he was awakened, and is mind and essence imbued into this blade.  The lich, Kangaxx, kept Mune with him all the time, and when Kangaxx was imprisoned, Mune was imprisoned with him.

Mune's essence permeates this blade, and grants whomever wields it, bonuses to Strength and Constitution.  Should Mune ever be reunited with his brother, their force would forge a weapon destined to strike fear into the heart of evil all throughout the realms.

STATISTICS

